  "description": "IRS Code 840 indicates a manual refund was issued outside normal automated processing. Learn what triggers manual refunds, how to verify delivery, and which companion codes to check.",
  "content": "<header class=\"mt-6\">\n      <div class=\"inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-full tm-kbd px-4 py-2 text-xs text-slate-300\">\n        <span class=\"font-semibold text-white\">IRS Transcript Codes</span>\n        <span class=\"text-slate-500\">•</span>\n        <span>Built for 750,000+ U.S. Tax Professionals</span>\n      </div>\n\n      <h1 class=\"mt-4 text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl\">IRS Code <span class=\"text-purple-300\">840</span> Meaning</h1>\n\n      <p class=\"mt-3 max-w-3xl text-base text-slate-300 tm-prose\">\n        IRS Code 840 marks a <strong>manual refund</strong>. Instead of a standard automated refund posting (often shown as <strong>Code 846</strong>), the IRS issued funds through an exception-based process. This page shows how to recognize 840 in context, verify delivery, and explain what happened to clients.\n      </p>\n\n      <div class=\"mt-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row sm:items-center\">\n        <button type=\"button\" data-open-sample class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-500 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-purple-400 transition\">View sample report</button>\n        <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400/30 transition\">Try the parser (requires credits)</a>\n      </div>\n    </header>\n\n    <!-- Main Content Grid -->\n    <section class=\"mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-3\">\n\n      <!-- Article Content -->\n      <article class=\"lg:col-span-2 tm-card rounded-2xl p-6 sm:p-8\">\n        <div class=\"tm-prose\">\n\n          <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">What is IRS Code 840?</h2>\n          <p class=\"mt-3 text-slate-300\"><strong>Plain-English definition:</strong> IRS Code 840 means the IRS issued a manual refund. The refund did not go out through the normal automated pipeline.</p>\n\n          <dl class=\"mt-5 grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2\">\n            <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Common transcript type</dt>\n              <dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Account Transcript</dd>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Usually appears near</dt>\n              <dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Codes 740, 841, 846</dd>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Typical context</dt>\n              <dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">Returned refunds, reissues, exceptions</dd>\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <dt class=\"text-xs font-semibold text-slate-300\">Client-friendly summary</dt>\n              <dd class=\"mt-1 text-sm text-white\">“The IRS reissued your refund manually”</dd>\n            </div>\n          </dl>\n\n          <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">When does Code 840 appear?</h2>\n          <ol class=\"mt-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-slate-300 space-y-2\">\n            <li><strong>Returned refund handling:</strong> A standard refund is returned as undeliverable and later reissued manually.</li>\n            <li><strong>Cancelled or reversed refund activity:</strong> A refund is cancelled and then reissued through an exception path.</li>\n            <li><strong>Special processing cases:</strong> Hardship or other exceptions may be processed via manual refund procedures.</li>\n          </ol>\n\n          <h2 class=\"mt-10 text-xl font-bold text-white\">What should a tax professional do next?</h2>\n          <ol class=\"mt-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-slate-300 space-y-2\">\n            <li><strong>Confirm amount and date:</strong> Match the 840 entry to the client’s expected refund and timing.</li>\n            <li><strong>Review companion codes:</strong> Check for 740 and 841 activity and whether an earlier 846 appears.</li>\n            <li><strong>Verify delivery details:</strong> Confirm address and bank details because manual refunds may be mailed as checks.</li>\n          </ol>\n\n          <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n          <h2 id=\"example\" class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">Example: how this looks in a parsed report</h2>\n          <p class=\"mt-2 text-slate-300\">Below is a simplified view of how Code 840 can appear in a client-ready transcript report:</p>\n\n          <div class=\"code-block mt-5\">\n            <div class=\"code-label\">Manual refund timeline example</div>\n            <div class=\"space-y-3 text-sm\">\n              <div>\n                <span class=\"code-key\">Code 846</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Refund issued</span><br>\n                <span class=\"text-slate-500 text-xs\">Amount: $900</span>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n                <span class=\"code-key\">Code 740</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Undeliverable refund returned</span><br>\n                <span class=\"text-slate-500 text-xs\">Amount: -$900</span>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n                <span class=\"code-key\">Code 841</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Refund cancelled</span><br>\n                <span class=\"text-slate-500 text-xs\">Amount: $900</span>\n              </div>\n              <div>\n                <span class=\"code-key\">Code 840</span> – <span class=\"text-slate-400\">Manual refund</span><br>\n                <span class=\"text-slate-500 text-xs\">Amount: $900</span>\n              </div>\n            </div>\n          </div>\n\n          <hr class=\"my-10 border-slate-800/60\">\n\n          <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-white\">FAQ</h2>\n          <div class=\"mt-4 space-y-4\">\n            <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">What does IRS Code 840 mean on a transcript?</summary>\n              <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Code 840 means the IRS issued a manual refund instead of using the standard automated refund process.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">Why would the IRS issue a manual refund instead of Code 846?</summary>\n              <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Manual refunds are used when standard processing does not apply, such as after returned or cancelled refunds or for certain exceptions.</p>\n            </details>\n\n            <details class=\"rounded-xl tm-soft p-4\">\n              <summary class=\"cursor-pointer text-sm font-semibold text-white\">How do I turn this into a client deliverable?</summary>\n              <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Generate a branded transcript report and include it as a consult deliverable. Local parsing, instant results, no upload needed.</p>\n            </details>\n          </div>\n\n        </div>\n      </article>\n\n      <!-- Sidebar -->\n      <aside class=\"space-y-6\">\n\n        <!-- CTA Card: Make This Billable -->\n        <div class=\"tm-card rounded-2xl p-6\">\n          <h2 class=\"text-base font-bold text-white\">Make this billable</h2>\n          <p class=\"mt-2 text-sm text-slate-300\">Convert transcripts into a clean report you can deliver with a consult. Local parsing. No upload.</p>\n          <button type=\"button\" data-open-sample class=\"mt-4 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-500 px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-slate-950 hover:bg-purple-400 transition\">View sample report</button>\n          <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"mt-3 inline-flex w-full items-center justify-center rounded-xl tm-soft px-4 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:border-slate-400